A dervish met a king. The king said： ‘Ask a boon of me.’ The dervish
replied： ‘I will not ask a boon from one of my slaves.’ ‘How is
that?’ said the king. The dervish said： ‘I have two slaves who are
thy masters： covetousness and expectation.’
